40
00:03:07,533 --> 00:03:11,315
So when I received this call from Commodore, I was

41
00:03:11,375 --> 00:03:11,976
astounded.

42
00:03:11,996 --> 00:03:12,796
And they said to me.

43
00:03:14,222 --> 00:03:15,722
Oh, we've heard about your company.

44
00:03:15,782 --> 00:03:16,742
And I thought, really?

45
00:03:16,762 --> 00:03:19,763
What, you've heard about our baked bean exporting company?

46
00:03:19,803 --> 00:03:21,744
Sounds unlikely, but anyway.

47
00:03:22,044 --> 00:03:23,164
I've heard about your company.

48
00:03:23,404 --> 00:03:25,765
Would you come up and be our guest for the day?

49
00:03:26,285 --> 00:03:28,165
And we'll show you around Commodore.

50
00:03:28,225 --> 00:03:31,066
And we want to talk about this new piece of hardware, the

51
00:03:31,106 --> 00:03:31,686
Amiga 1000.

52
00:03:33,927 --> 00:03:38,208
And so they brought me up, and with my business partner,

53
00:03:38,228 --> 00:03:39,188
